# Health baseline (OPTIONAL — tenant-supplied, never shipped with the skill)

Paste any clinical context you want OtenyFlatBellyTalent to take into account. This file is
**yours**: OtenyFlatBellyTalent only *reflects* what you put here and applies the safety
boundary (`../references/safety-boundaries.md`) — it never invents a diagnosis or a
lab value, and it never overrides your physician.

Leave blank / delete any line you don't want to share. The coach reads this if it
exists; nothing here is required to use the bot.

## Diagnoses (only what your doctor told you)
- e.g. fatty liver (NAFLD) confirmed YYYY-MM-DD
-

## Labs (value · unit · date) — for the coach to track improvement against
- e.g. ALAT  __ U/L  (YYYY-MM-DD)
- e.g. HDL   __ mmol/L (YYYY-MM-DD)
-

## Medications
- name · dose · since
-

## Notes for the coach
- e.g. "no alcohol while a liver marker is elevated", any clinician instructions
-

> Reminder: liver/cardiac markers are physician-owned. The coach frames them as
> confirmation that the daily food work is doing its job — not as a diagnosis.
